{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I call myself a body architect."},{"time":3000,"text":"I trained in classical ballet"},{"time":4000,"text":"and have a background in architecture and fashion."},{"time":7000,"text":"As a body architect, I fascinate with the human body"},{"time":10000,"text":"and explore how I can transform it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":13000,"text":"I worked at Philips Electronics"},{"time":16000,"text":"in the far-future design research lab,"},{"time":18000,"text":"looking 20 years into the future."},{"time":20000,"text":"I explored the human skin, and how technology can transform the body."},{"time":24000,"text":"I worked on concepts like an electronic tattoo,"},{"time":28000,"text":"which is augmented by touch,"},{"time":30000,"text":"or dresses that blushed and shivered with light."},{"time":33000,"text":"I started my own experiments."},{"time":36000,"text":"These were the low-tech approaches to the high-tech conversations I was having."},{"time":40000,"text":"These are Q-tips stuck to my roommate with wig glue."}]},{"cues":[{"time":44000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":47000,"text":"I started a collaboration with a friend of mine, Bart Hess --"},{"time":51000,"text":"he doesn't normally look like this --"},{"time":53000,"text":"and we used ourselves as models."},{"time":56000,"text":"We transformed our apartments into our laboratories,"},{"time":59000,"text":"and worked in a very spontaneous and immediate way."},{"time":62000,"text":"We were creating"},{"time":65000,"text":"visual imagery provoking human evolution."}]},{"cues":[{"time":67000,"text":"Whilst I was at Philips, we discussed this idea of a maybe technology,"},{"time":72000,"text":"something that wasn't either switched on or off, but in between."},{"time":75000,"text":"A maybe that could take the form of a gas or a liquid."},{"time":78000,"text":"And I became obsessed with this idea of blurring the perimeter of the body,"},{"time":82000,"text":"so you couldn't see where the skin ended and the near environment started."},{"time":86000,"text":"I set up my studio in the red-light district"},{"time":89000,"text":"and obsessively wrapped myself in plumbing tubing,"},{"time":92000,"text":"and found a way to redefine the skin"},{"time":95000,"text":"and create this dynamic textile."},{"time":97000,"text":"I was introduced to Robyn, the Swedish pop star,"},{"time":102000,"text":"and she was also exploring"},{"time":104000,"text":"how technology coexists with raw human emotion."},{"time":107000,"text":"And she talked about how technology with these new feathers,"},{"time":110000,"text":"this new face paint, this punk, the way that we identify with the world,"},{"time":113000,"text":"and we made this music video."}]},{"cues":[{"time":115000,"text":"I'm fascinated with the idea"},{"time":118000,"text":"of what happens when you merge biology with technology,"},{"time":121000,"text":"and I remember reading about this idea of being able to reprogram"},{"time":125000,"text":"biology, in the future, away from disease and aging."},{"time":128000,"text":"And I thought about this concept of,"},{"time":130000,"text":"imagine if we could reprogram"},{"time":132000,"text":"our own body odor, modify and biologically enhance it,"},{"time":136000,"text":"and how would that change the way that we communicate with each other?"},{"time":139000,"text":"Or the way that we attract sexual partners?"},{"time":142000,"text":"And would we revert back to being more like animals,"},{"time":144000,"text":"more primal modes of communication?"},{"time":146000,"text":"I worked with a synthetic biologist,"},{"time":149000,"text":"and I created a swallowable perfume,"},{"time":152000,"text":"which is a cosmetic pill that you eat"},{"time":155000,"text":"and the fragrance comes out through the skin's surface when you perspire."},{"time":159000,"text":"It completely blows apart the way that perfume is,"},{"time":163000,"text":"and provides a whole new format."},{"time":164000,"text":"It's perfume coming from the inside out."},{"time":167000,"text":"It redefines the role of skin, and our bodies become an atomizer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":170000,"text":"I've learned that there's no boundaries,"},{"time":174000,"text":"and if I look at the evolution of my work"},{"time":176000,"text":"i can see threads and connections that make sense."},{"time":180000,"text":"But when I look towards the future,"},{"time":182000,"text":"the next project is completely unknown and wide open."},{"time":185000,"text":"I feel like I have all these ideas existing embedded inside of me,"},{"time":189000,"text":"and it's these conversations and these experiences"},{"time":192000,"text":"that connect these ideas, and they kind of instinctively come out."}]},{"cues":[{"time":198000,"text":"As a body architect,"},{"time":200000,"text":"I've created this limitless and boundless platform"},{"time":202000,"text":"for me to discover whatever I want."},{"time":204000,"text":"And I feel like I've just got started."}]},{"cues":[{"time":207000,"text":"So here's to another day at the office."}]},{"cues":[{"time":210000,"text":"(Laughter) (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":213000,"text":"Thank you!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":216000,"text":"Thank you!"}]}]}